On January 31, 2022, the President signed the "Willie O'Ree Congressional Gold Medal Act" into law. This law grants Willie O'Ree, a former hockey player, the Congressional Gold Medal for his remarkable contributions and dedication to hockey, inclusion, and recreational opportunities. The President expressed gratitude to Senators Stabenow, Tim Scott, Schumer, and Casey, as well as Representatives Quigley, Pressley, and Emmer, for their leadership in making this recognition possible.